ough two parallel five-generation paths."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"ABCFM corporate member and Middlebury College trustee","body":"He served as a corporate member of the American Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions from 1840 and as a trustee of Middlebury College from 1834 to 1844. The ABCFM was the leading Protestant foreign-mission engine of the antebellum era; his presence on the corporate board placed him at its strategic center."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Son Elias named for missionary brother-in-law","body":"He named one son Elias Cornelius Hooker for his brother-in-law Rev Elias Cornelius — the ABCFM missionary who had married his sister Mary Ann Hooker. The name kept the missionary calling visible in the next generation, even though Cornelius himself died young in 1832."}],"number_of_marriages":2,"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST054","institution_blurb":"Middlebury College alumnus."},{"institution_id":"INST041","institution_blurb":"Corporate member of ABCFM from 1840."},{"institution_id":"INST137","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1817","institution_blurb":"Andover Theological Seminary 1817 — ordained Green's Farms CT 1821."}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Edward William Hooker","first_name":"Edward","last_name":"Hooker","middle_name":"William","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://images.findagrave.com/photos/2013/307/96378384_138361708435.jpg"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"edward-hooker-1794"},"HD2241":{"id":"HD2241","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":8,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"H01354","mother_id":"X00711"},"tags":[],"sourc